dcterms:description: Racing Kings is a game played on a Chess board with Chess pieces. The aim is to be the first player to move their King to the other end of the board. The game is modified by using fewer pieces and adjusting the starting position of the pieces.
dcterms:title: Racing Kings

dcterms:creator: T. Landau
dcterms:description: Reversi is a strategic board game played on an eight-by-eight square grid with pieces that have two distinct sides. The objective is to have more pieces on the board than the opponent when neither player can make a move.
dcterms:title: Reversi

dcterms:creator: D. Dugovic
dcterms:description: Stockfish is a multi-variant fork of the popular UCI chess engine, used as a reference opponent for the Racing Kings game.
dcterms:title: Stockfish

dcterms:description: The MCTS Player is based on Monte Carlo Tree Search methods, which are used for decision-making in games.
dcterms:title: MCTS Player
